‚çù NuGrid Borders Demo
‚çù Exercises the Border property on NuGrid: Border 1 (visible) vs Border 0 (none).
‚çù Two grids side by side with otherwise identical configuration.

 F‚Üê'F1'
 F eWC'Form' 'NuGrid Border Property'(50 50)(420 760)('Coord' 'Pixel')

‚çù Shared 3√ó2 data
 values‚Üê3 2‚ç¥'Alpha' 1 'Beta' 2 'Gamma' 3
 colTitles‚Üê'Name' 'Value'
 rowTitles‚Üê‚ç≥3

‚çù Left grid: Border 1 (default) ‚Äî visible 1px border around the grid
 (F,'.LBL1')eWC'Label' 'Border 1 (default)'(10 20)(20 200)
 (F,'.G1')eWC'NuGrid'('Posn'(40 20))('Size'(120 320))('Values' values)('ColTitles' colTitles)('RowTitles' rowTitles)('Border' 1)

‚çù Right grid: Border 0 ‚Äî grid renders with no outer border
 (F,'.LBL0')eWC'Label' 'Border 0 (no border)'(10 380)(20 200)
 (F,'.G0')eWC'NuGrid'('Posn'(40 380))('Size'(120 320))('Values' values)('ColTitles' colTitles)('RowTitles' rowTitles)('Border' 0)
